http://news.google.com/news/url?sa=T&ct=us/6-3&fd=R&url=http://www.news.com.au/couriermail/story/0,23739,21828620-23109,00.html&cid=1116840056&ei=m-xeRsngAYf40QHv7IzQDQ Suicide bomber kills 20 | The Courier-Mail Welcome to The Courier-Mail. Links from the paper Letter to the Editor Sell your car for free in print and online Place a classified newspaper ad Suicide bomber kills 20 By Fadhil al-Badrani in Falluja, Iraq May 31, 2007 09:07pm A SUICIDE bomber killed at least 20 people and wounded another 20 in the Iraqi city of Falluja today, police and hospital officials said. Falluja police spokesman Hamid Abid said the bomber, wearing a suicide explosives vest, walked up to a queue of about 150 young men at a police recruitment centre and blew himself up. Mr Abid put the total number of killed and wounded at between 45 and 50. Bilal Mohammed, a doctor at Falluja hospital, said 20 had been killed and 20 wounded. Falluja, 50km west of Baghdad, is in restive Anbar province, a stronghold of Sunni Arab insurgency. Recruitment centres for Iraqi security forces are common targets for such attacks, which are mostly blamed on Sunni Islamist al Qaeda. Some Sunni Arab tribes in Anbar have been encouraging young men to join the Iraqi security forces in Anbar as part of a new strategy to combat al Qaeda in the area. Al-Qaeda in turn has been waging a campaign against tribes who co-operate with authorities in Anbar. The US military has more than 6000 troops in Anbar, where local commanders have said that al Qaeda accounts for about 75 per cent of militants in and around Falluja. Also in World Breaking News Legal row over cow's mass grave death UK celebrates 40 years of Sgt Pepper Hewitt wins five-set comeback Putin claims 'US response' missile test Taliban kill 16 policeman Indon governor accepts Iemma apology Suicide bomber kills 20 Students apologise for humiliating teacher Japan's crown prince to have surgery Music giant puts free video archive online Russian poisoned by UK spies