ned at a nearby restaurant. Kate McCann said the Pope had some comforting words for them both. UK govt cell reviews Iraq kidnap crisis Lithuania backs missile shield in Europe, says country needs it Russia, US clash on Kosovo and missile plan Ukraine poll proposal faces another hurdle Japan rebuffs German G8 climate offer Sweden gets ‘Second Life’ on the Net Acquittal plea in air collision trial Thaksin barred from politics for 5 years Oz police spark row with Jakarta Malaysian loses bid to shed Islam Norway most peaceful nation S Leone welcomes hero Blair Hong Kong’s boom belies growing wealth gap Sikh priests reject apology over guru ads Tree newspaper blossoms in Darfur desert Back to the Top &#169; 2001 The Peninsula. for any content re-production. To advertise on the site, please get in touch with our Site designed and developed by:
